To demonstrate padding method (1 followed by zeros).
def pad(message, block_size):
    bits = ''.join(format(ord(c), '08b') for c in message)
    pad_len = block_size - (len(bits) % block_size)
    padding = "1" + "0" * (pad_len - 1)
    return bits + padding

msg = "HELLO"
block_size = 64

padded = pad(msg, block_size)
print("Padded message length:", len(padded))
print("Padded bits:", padded)
Result

Padding ensures that every message ends with hidden padding, preventing attackers from identifying message lengths or block patterns.
